{"name":"Beauty Domain","type":"subclass","img":"icons/magic/symbols/star-solid-gold.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"25\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Beauty Domain</span></h1><h4><strong>Restriction: Only Humans and Aasimar of the Empire of Arcotia</strong></h4><p>Only Humans and Aasimar of the Empire of Arcotia may choose this cleric subclass; however, your DM may remove this restriction if you are playing in another setting or for any other reason.</p><p>Some clerics of Vinoverno are so devoted to the High Star that their faith aims at nothing more than worshipping her, imitating her in everything and basking in her celestial perfection. Most of these clerics are maidens who hope, by imitating the High Star, to one day be chosen to serve in such a role; but there is also no shortage of young men who undertake this faith out of pure adoration of the High Star and imitate her because they see her as an ideal of perfection. What most strikes young people inexperienced in theology is precisely the celestial goodness and beauty of this divinity. These clerics - while sharing all other aspects of worship - focus on these points in particular and the High Star rewards their devotion by granting them its divine favour. A large part of the day is devoted to one's beauty routine, to choosing the most suitable attire for the occasion that best showcases one's aesthetic gifts: being beautiful is not only good for oneself but also good for others who enjoy the sight, what is good is beautiful. It is not surprising that the undead are so ugly while the High Star is so beautiful: beauty is synonymous with goodness.</p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h2 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"26\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Beauty Domain Spells</span></h2><table class=\"w-100 rd__table  stripe-odd-table\" style=\"width:100%;height:102px\"><thead style=\"text-shadow:1px 1px var(--color-shadow-dark);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\"><tr style=\"height:17px\"><th class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\">Cleric Level</th><th class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\">Spells</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">1st</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.eS7XnnApoxRxYXPs]{Charm Person}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ge3Saet9zPTDyaoL]{Heroism}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">3rd</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.30ZgXtijJVCxQk5N]{Enthrall}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.zMAWdyc8UVb37BK4]{Suggestion}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">5th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.BP3GCwa66IAw1yTG]{Daylight}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.6g3WLOZ2u0EbaLAd]{Hypnotic Pattern}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">7th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.9hQXdMSmerkTsHDe]{Confusion}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.VtCXMdyM6mAdIJZb]{Death Ward}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">9th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM]{Dominate Person}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Pyzmm8R7rVsNAPsd]{Mass Cure Wounds}</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"27\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">How Beautiful She Is</span></h1><p>Starting at 1st level, you become a symbol of beauty: opponents hesitate to even brush against you. As a bonus action, you can replicate the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.gvdA9nPuWLck4tBl]{Sanctuary} spell for one minute, but you can target only yourself. The DC is your spellcasting DC. You do not lose this bene-</p><p>fit if you cast spells that charm hostile creatures, as long as you do not deal damage. As long as this privilege is active, you give off bright light within a radius of 20 ft (6 m) and dim light for an additional 20 ft (6 m). You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all spent uses when you end a long rest.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">How Good She Is</span></h1><p>At 1st level, you gain proficiency in the abilities @skill[persuasion] and @skill[performance].</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"29\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Channel Divinity: Blinding Beauty</span></h1><p>Starting at 2nd level, you can use Channeling Divinity to invoke the beauty of the High Star.</p><p>As an action, you present your Holy Symbol and emit a sphere of holy light that dazzles enemies. Any hostile creature within 20 ft (6 m) must make a CON save against your spellcasting DC. If it fails, it is blinded for 1 minute. A creature may repeat the save at the end of its turn. If it passes, the effect on itself ends.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"30\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">How Generous She Is</span></h1><p>Starting at 6th level, your beauty refreshes spirits in timereactions of need.</p><p>As a reaction, when you or an allied creature within 30 ft (9 m) of you, that you can see, fails a save on INT, WIS,or CHA or a CHA-based ability check, you can allow the roll to be repeated, adding your WIS mod. to the result. You may use this privilege after you see the result but before the DM states whether the roll was successful or not. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain the spent uses when you complete a long rest.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"31\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Enhanced Cantrips</span></h1><p>Starting at 8th level, you add your WIS mod to the damage you deal with any cleric cantrip.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"32\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Astonishing Beauty</span></h1><p>Starting from the 17th level, as an action, you can decide to unleash the pure light of the High Star. You emit bright light within a radius of 150 ft (45 m) and dim light for an additional 150 ft (45 m). The light lasts for one minute or until you use an action to interrupt it. When you cast a spell and target only allied creatures you can ignore the range of the spell and choose targets from creatures within this light.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"iRdW","identifier":"beauty-domain","classIdentifier":"cleric","advancement":[{"_id":"wgZbzDAmXPAsLHHd","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.eS7XnnApoxRxYXPs","Compendium.dnd5e.spells.ge3Saet9zPTDyaoL"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"wis","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Domain Spells","icon":""},{"_id":"YKw38gJxp0SkMeKw","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Wkt1byueIXBouoZR","Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.8eSMcKkWV2pCKL9T"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"3tSxld1EsDLYOuVf","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.lgnBBdlqt3ie4mPL"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Feautures","icon":""},{"_id":"3OTO3EdQzqgof4Zx","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Z4TLGFbw7cXovzeT"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"zf3MTXE3YxFHlYpb","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.1HD8G4WGHiuPBdra"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":8,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"1a5IEznyxgOudP9D","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.8UYJICxUFG3jAbgu"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":17,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"qveGmUG8ERDNKD7O","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.30ZgXtijJVCxQk5N","Compendium.dnd5e.spells.zMAWdyc8UVb37BK4"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"wis","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":3,"title":"Domain Spells","icon":""},{"_id":"UnBtItL2mwRDImmj","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.9hQXdMSmerkTsHDe","Compendium.dnd5e.spells.VtCXMdyM6mAdIJZb"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"wis","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":5,"title":"Domain Spells","icon":""},{"_id":"GH8IiPRrHDWU6lVe","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.spells.91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM","Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Pyzmm8R7rVsNAPsd"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"wis","preparation":"always","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":9,"title":"Domain Spells","icon":""}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"full","ability":"wis"}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"kg10vII5VzQknnnc":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"deposito-pg","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.290","systemVersion":"2.0.3"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZ1DTVvITskkAGks"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670327806146,"modifiedTime":1670327806146,"lastModifiedBy":"kg10vII5VzQknnnc"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Unc5SOI4pXVBHEQ7"}
{"name":"Path of the Magic Denier","type":"subclass","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-orange.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"25\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Path of the Magic Denier</span></h1><h4><strong>Restriction: Only Dragonborn from Fo'Khar island</strong></h4><p>Only dragonborn from the Fo’Khar island can choose this barbarian subclass; however, your DM can remove this restriction if you are playing another setting or for any other reason.</p><p>Shur’Khan is the only god. Only Shur’Khan’s powers are real. Magic is weakness, magic is fiction. Among the dragonborn tribes of Fo’Khar Island it is common not to believe in magic that is not derived from the dragon god Shur’Khan.</p><p>A small circle of Fo’Khar barbarians is so firmly convinced of this conception that they repudiate magic to such an extent that it is weak against them and in some cases, even vain. Just as a druid does not wear metal on his skin because it is believed to be against the spirits, so the magic denier does not accept magic: he always rejects all forms of spells as an impure and unholy imitation of Shur’Khan.</p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Magic Denial</span></h1><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 3rd level, veneration toward the dragon god turns you away from magic, whether defensive or offensive. The number of magic items you can attune </span>to at the same time is 2.</p><p>While you are in rage, you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You become resistant to damage from spells and magical effects.</p></li><li><p>You have advantage on saves against spells and magical effects.</p></li><li><p>When you receive healing from a spell, you recover only half the normal HP.</p></li><li><p>You are considered unwilling when a spell affects you.</p></li></ul><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Wrathful Outburst</span></h1><p>Starting at 3rd level, as long as you are in rage, when a creature you can see casts a spell or magic effect, you can move toward it by half your movement speed after the spell or ability takes effect. You can no longer move this way until the beginning of your next turn.</p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Tenacity of Shur'Khan</span></h1><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 6th level, when you make a save against a spell or magical effect, you can choose to make a CON save instead of the required roll. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your CON mod. and you regain all spent uses when you complete a long rest.</span></p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Adversion to Magic</span></h1><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">At 10th level, your hatred of magic becomes so strong that you can wipe it out. As long as you are in rage, you can use the attack action to make a special attack to break a spell. If you are able to make multiple attacks through the attack action, this replaces one of them. Instead of making a roll to hit, you replicate the effects of a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.15Fa6q1nH27XfbR8]{Dispel Magic}. The range of the effect is equal to the range of the weapon you wield. The spellcasting characteristic for this effect is CON. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your CON mod. and you regain all spent u</span>ses when you end a long rest.</p><p>Also, when you deal damage to a creature concentrating on a spell, that creature suffers disadvantage on the save it makes to maintain concentration.</p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Avatar of Antimagic</span></h1><p>Starting at 14th level you emanate an aura that intimidates opponents and hinders them from using magical abilities.</p><p>When a hostile creature within 10 ft (3 m) of you casts a spell or uses a magical effect, it must make a WIS save.</p><p>The DC is equal to 8 + your CON mod + your proficiency bonus. If it fails, the spell or magic effect fails and has no effect.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"iRdW","identifier":"path-of-the-magic-denier","classIdentifier":"barbarian","advancement":[{"_id":"H1IJXl5EN3cliN2D","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.w9ek0H3cOgUQcSql","Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.hErYuHeXKxhWQiOz"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":3,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"lbgLeflMUxHpKgTB","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.UoHrW6iQ36fp3Wkd"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"YlAtpbtcJOLt4INc","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.yBazwSfjCYy0O8rA"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"AUm9i05kvmONNIuz","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.W0TGOhdiMiJPPiih"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","icon":""}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"kg10vII5VzQknnnc":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ihJvcmq5J6DxeCix"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332120850,"modifiedTime":1670333942558,"lastModifiedBy":"kg10vII5VzQknnnc"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Lbe63dSh0aEN1TAC"}
{"name":"Archivist","type":"subclass","img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-wall-blue.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"25\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Archivist</span></h1><h4><strong>Restriction: Only Elves from Ornwelun island</strong></h4><p>Only elves from the Ornwelun island can choose this wizard subclass; however, your DM can remove this restriction if you are playing another setting or for any other reason.</p><p>After a lifetime of isolation, devoted to study in the dusty libraries of Ornwelun, the most knowledgeable wizards are awarded the rank of archivist. These elderly scholars, find their power in the infinite theoretical knowledge of the arcane arts and possess grimoires filled with spells to suit every need.</p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Arcane Erudite</span></h1><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 2nd level, the time and money you spend copying a spell into your spellbook is halved.</span></p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Academic</span></h1><p>At 2nd level, you learn to speak, read and write two languages of your choice. In addition, you gain one of the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You gain proficiency in two of the following abilities (your choice):@skill[arcana], @skill[nature], @skill[religion], or @skill[history].</p></li><li><p>Choose one of your proficiency in Intelligence-based abilities (except Investigation). Your proficiency bonus doubles for each skill check made using your chosen skill.</p></li></ul><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Meticulous Preparation</span></h1><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 6th level, when you complete a long rest, you can prepare an extra number of spells equal to your proficiency bonus. The spells must be of a level with which you have spell slots.</span></p><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Mental Archives</span></h1></div><p>Starting at 10th level, if you spend 10 minutes studying your spellbook, you can replace a number of wizard spells - equal to your proficiency bonus - that you have prepared, with different spells - of a level in which you have spell slots - in your book. You can use this privilege once, and you cannot do so until you complete a long rest.</p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><h1 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" style=\"border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"28\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Eclectic Research</span></h1><p>At 14th level, you can learn magic of any kind and form. Choose, and add to your spellbook, two spells of any class that belong to a level at which you are able to cast spells, as indicated in the class table, or a cantrip. The spells you choose count as wizard spells exclusively for you and cannot be transcribed by other wizards.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"iRdW","identifier":"archivist","classIdentifier":"wizard","advancement":[{"_id":"oMXEs3PXnMuKKQUt","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.opukIwmwzYEfVcHX","Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.dkBE0tGoOA537MEW"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"mNggFRS4VVrdZ2B2","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.96dvgSfANPinZLUb"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"UrXJytlqcLrsZaey","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.BeCms9dGoRwiV2ye"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","icon":""},{"_id":"qR1K2XuVZ3WXl5Pp","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Mhzudj4sDV8nhAi3"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","icon":""}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"full","ability":"int"}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"kg10vII5VzQknnnc":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ihJvcmq5J6DxeCix"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332120850,"modifiedTime":1670341352105,"lastModifiedBy":"kg10vII5VzQknnnc"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"UwOtI9u6O4IQyQE4"}
